content: This contribution hasn’t received enough positive votes from the community. The "FASTEST" option has therefore been deactivated.

This clash is good, but the statement is currently very unclear.

This bit is so important but you don't actually explain what the numbers in parentheses mean, so clashers are forced to work it out from the test cases:
"There are 8 ranks :

F (1), E (15), D (30), C (50), B (70), A (80), S (90), National (100)"

You need to explain that the ranks are determined by your level and that F is levels 1-14, E is levels 15-29, ... etc.

I just got this in a clash and only me and the bots solved it. The other humans both got 0%.

A basic change I would suggest is to change the part I mentioned to the below:

"There are 8 ranks, which correspond to levels (in brackets) as below:

F (1-14), E (15-29), D (30-49), C (50-69), B (70-79), A (80-89), S (90-99), National (100-150)"

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: all good

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Noice , very fun level ;)

I don't understand the relationship between ranks and steps as it is unclear.  If you mean that the developer has to have 80 levels to be rank A, 30 levels to be rank D, then please state so.

You could change "There are 8 ranks.  Here are the ranks with their associated minimal level: Rank F (level 1) , Rank E (level 15) , ...

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: c'est un tres bon jeu pour les clash of code surtout pour les debutant

Goal
* Please change "more" to "better".

* Suggest to delete "These".

* Please delete ", determined by these step levels".

* Please add "One rank corresponds to one step. For example, [[step]] is 1 when [[rank]] is {{F}}, 2 when [[rank]] is {{E}}, and so on."

Output
* Please specify the exact output formats required. For example, Line 1 becomes:

<<Line 1:>> {{Rank = }}[[rank]] (rank associated to the [[next_level]])

* Please rewrite Line 2 similarly.

Stub generator
* Please add a write statement (e.g. "write answer").

Thanks.
I've made the changes. Thanks for your suggestions.
